jbt.model.task.leaf
Class ModelPerformInterruption

java.lang.Object
  jbt.model.core.ModelTask
      jbt.model.task.leaf.ModelLeaf
          jbt.model.task.leaf.ModelPerformInterruption

public class ModelPerformInterruption
extends ModelLeaf

A ModelPerformInterruption is a task that interacts with a ModelInterrupter decorator, interrupting it when it (the ModelPerformInterruption) is spawned. A ModelPerformInterruption always succeeds when it is spawned. When the ModelInterrupter gets interrupted, the status code it returns is also set by the ModelPerformInterruption.
